Silverman&rsquo;s rule of thumb for kernel density estimation bandwidth selection:
$$ h = 0.9 \cdot \min ( \hat{\sigma}, IQR/1.35 ) n^{-1/5} $$ Reference B. W. Silverman “Density Estimation for Statistics and Data Analysis” (1986) // Publisher: Chapman &amp; Hall, London.
Bib @Article{silverman1986, title = {Density Estimation for Statistics and Data Analysis}, publisher = {Chapman &amp;amp; Hall, London}, author = {Silverman, B. W.}, year = {1986} }

Scott&rsquo;s rule of thumb for kernel density estimation bandwidth selection.
$$ h \approx 1.06 \cdot \hat{\sigma} n^{-1/5} $$ Reference David W. Scott “Multivariate Density Estimation: Theory, Practice, and Visualization” (1992) // Wiley Series in Probability and Statistics. Publisher: Wiley. ISBN: 9780470316849. DOI: 10.1002/9780470316849
